meanings.definition: ボホール島（フィリピン中部の島）
meanings.english_definition: An island province of the Philippines located in the Central Visayas region.

examples.sentence: We visited the Chocolate Hills in Bohol.
examples.translation: 私たちはボホール島のチョコレートヒルズを訪れました。

etymology.value: The origin of the name "Bohol" is uncertain, but it is believed to have come from the word "Bo-ol", the name of a barangay (village) in the town of Baclayon.
